### Describe the bug

SvelteKit does use `moduleResolution: moduleResolution` by default from [v2](https://github.com/sveltejs/kit/releases/tag/%40sveltejs%2Fkit%402.0.0).

However, I had no problems using modules as `NodeNext` other than this issue.

I hope theses compiler options are supported as well.

```jsonc
// tsconfig.json
{
  "extends": "./.svelte-kit/tsconfig.json",
  "compilerOptions": {
    // ...
    "module": "NodeNext", // added
    "moduleResolution": "NodeNext" // updated
  }
}
```

```ts
// src/routes/fruits/[page=fruit]/+page.ts
export const load = ({ params }) => {
  // before: "apple" | "orange"
  // after: any
  const page = params.page;
};
```

